<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="170" pageId="18" pageNumber="169" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1300,2010]" box="[199,1009,1444,1471]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1444,1470]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Description.</emphasis>
Small specimen 4.6 (4.3) mm long and 0.6 (0.7) mm wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1300,2010]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">
Transverse prostomium attached to dorsal surface of base of upper lip; basal part as thick crest across dorsum, extending laterally and dorsally, covering SG1 laterally and terminating lateral to lower lip; distal part extending along upper lip, terminating subdistally. Buccal tentacles of two 
<typeStatus box="[865,927,1553,1579]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">types</typeStatus>
, long grooved annulated and uniformly cylindrical ones, short thick grooved and distally enlarged ones (
<figureCitation box="[813,896,1588,1614]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,633,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-185@19.[151,1435,633,1700]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Polycirrus idex n. sp. holotype MNHN-IA-TYPE 2015A. Anterior end, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Anterior end, ventral view, methyl green staining; D. Notochaetae, SG7, 40x objective. Abbreviations: Bt, buccal tentacle; Ll, lower lip; Ul, upper lip." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Figs 12</figureCitation>
A–B; 13A). Peristomium forming lips; upper lip elongate, longer than wide, with single median lobe only (
<figureCitation box="[799,882,1624,1650]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,633,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-185@19.[151,1435,633,1700]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Polycirrus idex n. sp. holotype MNHN-IA-TYPE 2015A. Anterior end, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Anterior end, ventral view, methyl green staining; D. Notochaetae, SG7, 40x objective. Abbreviations: Bt, buccal tentacle; Ll, lower lip; Ul, upper lip." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Figs 12</figureCitation>
B–C; 13A); lower lip oblong, slightly longer than wide, very glandular, ridged (
<figureCitation box="[481,588,1660,1686]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,633,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-185@19.[151,1435,633,1700]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Polycirrus idex n. sp. holotype MNHN-IA-TYPE 2015A. Anterior end, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Anterior end, ventral view, methyl green staining; D. Notochaetae, SG7, 40x objective. Abbreviations: Bt, buccal tentacle; Ll, lower lip; Ul, upper lip." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Figs 12C</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[600,652,1660,1686]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-23@20.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Polycirrus idex n. sp., SEM paratype AM W.53127. A. Anterior end, ventral view; B. Notopodia, SG8, ventral view; C. Notochaetae, SG8; D. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: Ll, lower lip; Ne, neuropodia, Ul, upper lip. Numbers refer to segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">13A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1300,2010]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">
SG1 and 2 reduced, SG2 visible ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[700,810,1696,1722]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,633,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-185@19.[151,1435,633,1700]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Polycirrus idex n. sp. holotype MNHN-IA-TYPE 2015A. Anterior end, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Anterior end, ventral view, methyl green staining; D. Notochaetae, SG7, 40x objective. Abbreviations: Bt, buccal tentacle; Ll, lower lip; Ul, upper lip." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Figs 12C</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[824,876,1696,1722]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-23@20.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Polycirrus idex n. sp., SEM paratype AM W.53127. A. Anterior end, ventral view; B. Notopodia, SG8, ventral view; C. Notochaetae, SG8; D. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: Ll, lower lip; Ne, neuropodia, Ul, upper lip. Numbers refer to segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">13A</figureCitation>
); body slightly broader until SG7. Ventro-lateral inflated pads well-defined from SG3 to SG9 (SG8), less defined on SG10 (SG9), smooth (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1286,1732,1758]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,633,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-185@19.[151,1435,633,1700]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Polycirrus idex n. sp. holotype MNHN-IA-TYPE 2015A. Anterior end, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Anterior end, ventral view, methyl green staining; D. Notochaetae, SG7, 40x objective. Abbreviations: Bt, buccal tentacle; Ll, lower lip; Ul, upper lip." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Figs 12C</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1299,1351,1732,1758]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-23@20.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Polycirrus idex n. sp., SEM paratype AM W.53127. A. Anterior end, ventral view; B. Notopodia, SG8, ventral view; C. Notochaetae, SG8; D. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: Ll, lower lip; Ne, neuropodia, Ul, upper lip. Numbers refer to segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">13A</figureCitation>
). Large anterior mid-ventral groove from S3, present until end of body as a stripe (
<figureCitation box="[986,1093,1768,1794]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,633,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-185@19.[151,1435,633,1700]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Polycirrus idex n. sp. holotype MNHN-IA-TYPE 2015A. Anterior end, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Anterior end, ventral view, methyl green staining; D. Notochaetae, SG7, 40x objective. Abbreviations: Bt, buccal tentacle; Ll, lower lip; Ul, upper lip." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Figs 12C</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1105,1157,1768,1794]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-23@20.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Polycirrus idex n. sp., SEM paratype AM W.53127. A. Anterior end, ventral view; B. Notopodia, SG8, ventral view; C. Notochaetae, SG8; D. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: Ll, lower lip; Ne, neuropodia, Ul, upper lip. Numbers refer to segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">13A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1300,2010]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">
Notopodia from SG3, extending for 13 (14) segments, until SG15 (SG16); not very elongate, rectangular, first pair slightly shorter, bilobed, postchaetal lobe conical with rounded tip, larger than prechaetal one (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1423,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1599,1623]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,187,1570]" captionTargetId="figure-19@27.[151,1436,181,1575]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18. Polycirrus readi n. sp., additional material MNHN-IA-PNT 124 (A–B), holotype MNHN-IA-TYPE 2019 (C–D). A. Entire specimen, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view, methyl green staining; C. Anterior end, lateral view; D. Anterior end, ventral view.; E. Notochaetae, SG8, 40x objective; F. Uncini, posterior chaetiger, 40x objective.Abbreviations: Bt, buccal tentacles; Ll, lower lip; Ul, upper lip; Sp, subrostral process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418517" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418517/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Winged notochaetae in two rows (
<figureCitation box="[544,654,1876,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1724,1748]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,633,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-185@19.[151,1435,633,1700]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Polycirrus idex n. sp. holotype MNHN-IA-TYPE 2015A. Anterior end, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Anterior end, ventral view, methyl green staining; D. Notochaetae, SG7, 40x objective. Abbreviations: Bt, buccal tentacle; Ll, lower lip; Ul, upper lip." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418505/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Figs 12D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[668,695,1876,1902]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-23@20.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Polycirrus idex n. sp., SEM paratype AM W.53127. A. Anterior end, ventral view; B. Notopodia, SG8, ventral view; C. Notochaetae, SG8; D. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: Ll, lower lip; Ne, neuropodia, Ul, upper lip. Numbers refer to segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">13</figureCitation>
B–C). Neuropodia beginning from SG8 (SG7); uncini with short occipitum and slightly convex base (
<typeStatus box="[570,627,1912,1938]" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Type</typeStatus>
1), crest with single elongate and sharp tooth on first row above main fang, with one additional row of 4–5 short, irregularly sized teeth (
<figureCitation box="[915,1020,1948,1974]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-23@20.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Polycirrus idex n. sp., SEM paratype AM W.53127. A. Anterior end, ventral view; B. Notopodia, SG8, ventral view; C. Notochaetae, SG8; D. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: Ll, lower lip; Ne, neuropodia, Ul, upper lip. Numbers refer to segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
), subrostral process present as small tooth (
<figureCitation box="[224,328,1984,2010]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-23@20.[151,1436,181,1887]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Polycirrus idex n. sp., SEM paratype AM W.53127. A. Anterior end, ventral view; B. Notopodia, SG8, ventral view; C. Notochaetae, SG8; D. Abdominal uncini. Abbreviations: Ll, lower lip; Ne, neuropodia, Ul, upper lip. Numbers refer to segments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4418507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4418507/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="169">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,151,609]" box="[199,652,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Nephridial and genital papillae not seen.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,151,609]" box="[199,415,187,213]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Pygidium rounded.</paragraph>
