<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,151,609]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,439,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Remarks.</emphasis>
With 14 segments with notopodia and neuropodia starting on SG7–8, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lavesque &amp; Hutchings &amp; Daffe &amp; Londoño-Mesa, 2020" authorityName="Lavesque &amp; Hutchings &amp; Daffe &amp; Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2020" box="[1112,1187,439,465]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Polycirrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="idex" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1112,1187,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">P. idex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1194,1258,439,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1194,1258,439,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from all other European species (
<tableCitation box="[429,517,475,501]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="29.[115,203,464,490]" captionText="TABLE 2. Distinguishing characters of European species of Polycirrus (Annelida: Polycirridae). MT: main tooth, SG: segment." pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Table 2</tableCitation>
). The closest species is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cepeda &amp; Lattig" authorityYear="2016" box="[790,939,475,500]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Polycirrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="asturiensis">
<emphasis box="[790,939,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">P. asturiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(notopodia on 10 segments and neuropodia starting on SG6) but this last species has a trefoiled upper lip (instead of a single lobe only for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lavesque &amp; Hutchings &amp; Daffe &amp; Londoño-Mesa, 2020" authorityName="Lavesque &amp; Hutchings &amp; Daffe &amp; Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2020" box="[1191,1264,511,537]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Polycirrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="idex" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1191,1264,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">P. idex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1270,1331,511,537]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1270,1331,511,537]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), a lower lip wider than long (instead of longer than wide for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lavesque &amp; Hutchings &amp; Daffe &amp; Londoño-Mesa, 2020" authorityName="Lavesque &amp; Hutchings &amp; Daffe &amp; Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2020" box="[732,807,547,573]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Polycirrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="idex" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[732,807,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">P. idex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[814,877,547,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[814,877,547,573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) and uncini showing two rows of secondary teeth above the main tooth (instead of a single row of secondary teeth for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lavesque &amp; Hutchings &amp; Daffe &amp; Londoño-Mesa, 2020" authorityName="Lavesque &amp; Hutchings &amp; Daffe &amp; Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2020" box="[915,990,583,609]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Polycirrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="idex" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[915,990,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">P. idex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[997,1059,583,609]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[997,1059,583,609]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
